Championship Gaming Series.label: Championship Gaming Series
Championship Gaming Series.description: The Championship Gaming Series was an international electronic sports league based in the United States of America, though it had expanded to every continent except Antarctica for Season Two before being abruptly discontinued. Wikipedia

Cyberathlete Professional League.label: Cyberathlete Professional League
Cyberathlete Professional League.description: The Cyberathlete Professional League, founded by Angel Munoz on June 27, 1997, is a professional sports tournament organization specializing in computer and console video game competitions. Wikipedia

Major League Gaming.label: Major League Gaming
Major League Gaming.description: Major League Gaming, founded in 2002 by Sundance DiGiovanni and Mike Sepso, is a North American professional Electronic sports organization, headquartered in New York City, New York. Wikipedia
